    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.3.31-32"/>
                <note type="curatorial">31</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection [1922]</note>
                <fw type="authorial">
                    <figure/>
                    THE WEST WEST HOTEL CO. 
                    T. P. M. 
                    SIOUX CITY
                    IOWA 
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    
                    <dateline>
                        Sunday Oct. 1
                    </dateline> 
                    
                    <salute>Dear Ones:-</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Yesterday P.m on the way to Wayne I saw Mrs. Brown &amp; Ruth for about 3 minutes they asked all about you folks. Ruth had two big red apples for me, and I judge that she polished them all the way to the station!</p> 
                <p>Was with Doctor last night. Left there at 2:45 this P.M. couldn't make connection here tomorrow. Will stay here tonight. Leave tomorrow at :45 a.m. for aberdeen. Will arrive at 10:55 P.M. It's 71 miles norht of Soo City-371 South of Omaha.</p> 
                <p>I hope everything is all right you. I'll be glad when stay at home. make &amp; peg steadily at the Cycle. I'm glad I can make every <unclear/> <unclear/> <del/> <unclear/></p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.3.31-32"/>
                <note type="curatorial">32</note>
                
                <p>This way, just the same.</p> 
                <p>It seems I never get on a train any more without meeting at least one person I know. Have had good campanions all the way so far.</p> 
                <p>Dont forget to mail Journal work on Wednesdays by noon. When I get back to Omaha I'll send some money, for <unclear/>.</p> 
                <p>Don't expect individual letters. I'll tell you about Lulu, Mama, when I get back to Omaha. Maybe I can write from Cedar Rapids on Thursdays Kiss the <unclear/> for Dad and thank her every day.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Lots of love to all of you</salute> 
                    <signed>Daddy.</signed>
                </closer> 
            </div1>
        </body>
        
